In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 1, 2015, as Law Day, U.S.A. He emphasizes the importance of the rule of law in maintaining a safe and just society. The article also highlights the 800th anniversary of the Magna Carta, which influenced the rights and liberties outlined in America's founding documents. The Magna Carta has also served as a basis for constitutional democracies worldwide. President Obama expresses his commitment to supporting good governance and the rule of law globally. He calls upon all Americans to recognize the significance of the legal and judicial systems and participate in activities to commemorate Law Day.